  "title": "Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p>1. Perform installation, commissioning, maintenance, troubleshooting, and repair of machinery/equipment.</p><p>2. Conduct routine inspections and ensure all systems operate efficiently and safely.</p><p>3. Attend service calls and provide on-site technical support to clients.</p><p>4. Diagnose mechanical/electrical faults and recommend corrective actions.</p><p>5. Prepare accurate service reports, job sheets, and documentation after each task.</p><p>6. Coordinate with the engineering/operations team on follow-up works and spare-partrequirements.</p><p>7. Manage and track tools, equipment, and spare parts used during service visits.</p><p>8. Provide technical advice to customers and maintain strong client relationships.</p><p>9. Ensure all work is completed in compliance with safety standards and company procedures.</p><p>10. Support project teams when required, including testing and commissioning activities.</p>",
